## Brain Platform Architecture - Detailed Exploration Report

I've conducted a thorough exploration of the Brain platform codebase to understand integration points for a coding agent orchestrator feature. Here are my detailed findings:

---

### 1. SERVER ARCHITECTURE

**Entry Point:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/server.ts`
- Simple entry that calls `startServer()` from `app/src/server/runtime/start-server.ts`

**Server Setup Pattern:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/src/server/runtime/start-server.ts`
- **Route registration:** Bun.serve with explicit routes object (no Express-style middleware)
- **Middleware pattern:** `withRequestLogging()` wraps all handlers for structured logging and error boundaries
- **Handler composition:** Each route creates handlers via factory functions that accept `ServerDependencies`
- **SSE support:** Centralized `SseRegistry` manages message streams for all agents

**Route Structure:**
```typescript
routes: {
  "/api/chat/messages": { POST: withRequestLogging(...) },
  "/api/mcp/:workspaceId/sessions/start": { POST: withRequestLogging(...) },
  // ... more routes
}
```

**HTTP Middleware Pattern:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/src/server/http/request-logging.ts`
- Wraps handlers with request context (request ID, method, route)
- Provides top-level error boundary
- Logs request lifecycle (received → completed/failed)
- Returns all responses with `x-request-id` header

---

### 2. AGENT SESSION TRACKING

**Schema Definition:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/schema/surreal-schema.surql` (lines 192-213)

```sql
DEFINE TABLE agent_session SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD agent ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD started_at ON agent_session TYPE datetime;
DEFINE FIELD ended_at ON agent_session TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON agent_session TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD project ON agent_session TYPE option<record<project>>;
DEFINE FIELD task_id ON agent_session TYPE option<record<task>>;
DEFINE FIELD summary ON agent_session TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD decisions_made ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<decision>>>;
DEFINE FIELD questions_asked ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<question>>>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed ON agent_session TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].task_id ON agent_session TYPE record<task>;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].from_status ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD tasks_progressed[*].to_status ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed ON agent_session TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].path ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].change_type ON agent_session TYPE string ASSERT $value IN ["created", "modified", "deleted"];
DEFINE FIELD observations_logged ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<observation>>>;
DEFINE INDEX agent_session_workspace ON agent_session FIELDS workspace;
DEFINE INDEX agent_session_project ON agent_session FIELDS project;
DEFINE INDEX agent_session_started_at ON agent_session FIELDS started_at;
```

**Lifecycle Functions:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/src/server/mcp/mcp-queries.ts`

**`createAgentSession()`** (async function):
- Creates agent_session record with `agent`, `started_at`, `workspace`, optional `project`, optional `task_id`
- Returns `{ session_id: string }`
- If task-scoped: auto-promotes task status from "todo"/"ready" → "in_progress", links via `source_session`

**`endAgentSession()`** (async function):
- Updates session with `ended_at`, `summary`
- Persists arrays: `decisions_made`, `questions_asked`, `tasks_progressed`, `files_changed`, `observations_logged`
- Creates `produced`, `asked`, `progressed` relation edges from session to entities
- Returns `{ session_id: string; ended: boolean }`

---

### 3. AUTHORITY FRAMEWORK

**Authority System:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/src/server/iam/authority.ts`

**AuthorityAction Types:**
```typescript
"create_decision" | "confirm_decision" | "create_task" | "complete_task" |
"create_observation" | "acknowledge_observation" | "resolve_observation" |
"create_question" | "create_suggestion"
```

**AuthorityPermission Levels:**
- `"auto"` — Agent can act directly
- `"provisional"` — Agent output marked as provisional, requires human review
- `"propose"` — Agent can only propose (returns 403 `AuthorityError`)
- `"blocked"` — Agent forbidden (returns 403 `AuthorityError`)

**Authority Scope Table:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/schema/surreal-schema.surql` (lines 456-471)
```sql
DEFINE TABLE authority_scope SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD agent_type ON authority_scope TYPE string
  ASSERT $value IN ["code_agent", "architect", "management", "design_partner", "observer"];
DEFINE FIELD action ON authority_scope TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD permission ON authority_scope TYPE string
  ASSERT $value IN ["auto", "provisional", "propose", "blocked"];
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON authority_scope TYPE option<record<workspace>>;
DEFINE INDEX authority_scope_lookup ON authority_scope
  FIELDS agent_type, action, workspace UNIQUE;
```

**Permission Resolution:** `checkAuthority()` function
1. Queries workspace-specific override if `workspaceRecord` provided
2. Falls back to global default (workspace IS NONE)
3. Returns "blocked" if no row found (fail-safe)

**Agent Type Mapping:** `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/richmond/app/src/server/chat/tools/types.ts`
```typescript
type AgentType = "code_agent" | "architect" | "management" | "design_partner" | "observer";
```

**Default mappings in authority.ts:**
```typescript
const ACTOR_DEFAULT_AGENT_TYPE = {
  pm_agent: "management",
  analytics_agent: "observer",
};
```

