Execute *design-architecture for the "coding-agent-orchestrator" feature. All discovery questions have been answered. Produce the full deliverables now.

## Confirmed Decisions

**Q1: OpenCode interaction model → Pattern B (on-demand spawn)**
- Brain lazily spawns the OpenCode server on first agent assignment via `createOpencodeServer()` from `@opencode-ai/sdk`
- `createOpencodeServer()` spawns `opencode serve` as a managed child process via `node:child_process.spawn()`
- Brain caches the client, kills the process on shutdown via `AbortController`
- Config injected via `OPENCODE_CONFIG_CONTENT` env var (includes MCP servers, providers, model config)

**Q2: Git management → Git worktrees**
- Brain creates a git worktree per task at e.g. `.brain/worktrees/agent-{taskSlug}` on branch `agent/{taskSlug}`
- OpenCode client gets `directory: worktreePath` pointing to the worktree
- Agent works entirely within the isolated worktree
- On accept → merge branch, remove worktree
- On reject with feedback → agent continues in same worktree
- On abort → remove worktree + branch

**Q3: Diff for review → Git diff from worktree branch**
- Natural consequence of worktree approach: `git diff main...agent/{taskSlug}`
- No need for event accumulation in walking skeleton

**Quality Attributes (confirmed ranking):**
1. Maintainability — solo dev, extend existing patterns
2. Reliability — no orphaned processes, deterministic cleanup
3. Operability — observable agent activity, stall detection
4. Security — authority-scoped agents
5. Performance — <5s session creation, <1s SSE latency

**Development Paradigm:** Functional-leaning TypeScript (factory functions, composition, no classes beyond AI SDK's ToolLoopAgent)

## OpenCode SDK API Surface (from source analysis)

### Server
```typescript
// @opencode-ai/sdk/server
import { spawn } from "node:child_process";

type ServerOptions = {
    hostname?: string;  // default "127.0.0.1"
    port?: number;      // default 4096
    signal?: AbortSignal;
    timeout?: number;   // default 5000ms
    config?: Config;    // injected via OPENCODE_CONFIG_CONTENT env var
};

function createOpencodeServer(options?: ServerOptions): Promise<{
    url: string;
    close(): void;  // kills child process
}>;

// Convenience: spawn server + create client
function createOpencode(options?: ServerOptions): Promise<{
    client: OpencodeClient;
    server: { url: string; close(): void; };
}>;
```

### Client
```typescript
// @opencode-ai/sdk/client
function createOpencodeClient(config?: Config & { directory?: string }): OpencodeClient;

// OpencodeClient has these class-based namespaces:
// client.session.create(), .list(), .status(), .delete(), .get(), .update(), .chat(), .abort(), .summarize()
// client.global.event() — SSE event stream
// client.project.list(), .current()
// client.config.get(), .update(), .providers()
// client.tool.ids(), .list()
// client.file.read()
// client.mcp.connect(), .disconnect()
// client.event.subscribe() — per-session event subscription
```

### Key Types
```typescript
type Session = {
    id: string;
    path: { cwd: string; root: string; };
    title: string;
    version: string;
    time: { created: number; updated: number; compacting?: number; };
};

type SessionCreateData = {
    body?: { parentID?: string; title?: string; };
    query?: { directory?: string; };
};

type UserMessage = {
    id: string; sessionID: string; role: "user";
    summary?: { title?: string; body?: string; diffs: Array<FileDiff>; };
    agent: string;
    model: { providerID: string; modelID: string; };
};

type AssistantMessage = {
    id: string; sessionID: string; role: "assistant";
    time: { created: number; completed?: number; };
    error?: ProviderAuthError | UnknownError | MessageAbortedError | ApiError;
    cost: number;
    tokens: { input: number; output: number; reasoning: number; cache: { read: number; write: number; }; };
};

type FileDiff = { file: string; before: string; after: string; additions: number; deletions: number; };

// Event types (SSE stream from client.global.event()):
type Event = 
    | EventSessionCreated    // { type: "session.created", properties: { info: Session } }
    | EventSessionUpdated    // { type: "session.updated", properties: { info: Session } }
    | EventSessionDeleted    // { type: "session.deleted", properties: { info: Session } }
    | EventSessionDiff       // { type: "session.diff", properties: { ... } }
    | EventSessionError      // session-level errors
    | EventMessageUpdated    // { type: "message.updated", properties: { info: Message } }
    | EventMessagePartUpdated // { type: "message.part.updated", properties: { info: Part } }
    | EventFileEdited        // file change events
    | EventVcsBranchUpdated  // branch changes
    | EventPermissionUpdated // permission requests
    | EventPermissionReplied // permission responses
    | ...more
```

## Existing Codebase Architecture (from exploration)

### Server Architecture
- **Runtime**: Bun.serve with explicit routes object in `app/src/server/runtime/start-server.ts`
- **Handler pattern**: Factory functions accepting `ServerDependencies`, wrapped with `withRequestLogging()`
- **Entry**: `app/server.ts` → `startServer()` from runtime

### ServerDependencies Type
```typescript
type ServerDependencies = {
    config: ServerConfig;
    surreal: Surreal;
    analyticsSurreal: Surreal;
    auth: Auth;
    chatAgentModel: any;
    extractionModel: any;
    pmAgentModel: any;
    analyticsAgentModel: any;
    embeddingModel: any;
    sse: SseRegistry;
};
```

### Agent Session Table (existing schema)
```sql
DEFINE TABLE agent_session SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD agent ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD started_at ON agent_session TYPE datetime;
DEFINE FIELD ended_at ON agent_session TYPE option<datetime>;
DEFINE FIELD workspace ON agent_session TYPE record<workspace>;
DEFINE FIELD project ON agent_session TYPE option<record<project>>;
DEFINE FIELD task_id ON agent_session TYPE option<record<task>>;
DEFINE FIELD summary ON agent_session TYPE option<string>;
DEFINE FIELD decisions_made ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<decision>>>;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed ON agent_session TYPE option<array<object>>;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].path ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD files_changed[*].change_type ON agent_session TYPE string;
DEFINE FIELD observations_logged ON agent_session TYPE option<array<record<observation>>>;
DEFINE INDEX agent_session_workspace ON agent_session FIELDS workspace;
```

### Authority Framework (existing)
- `iam/authority.ts` — `checkAuthority()` resolves permissions
- Permission levels: `auto`, `provisional`, `propose`, `blocked`
- Agent types enum already includes `code_agent`
- `authority_scope` table with workspace-specific overrides

### SSE Registry (existing)
```typescript
type SseRegistry = {
    registerMessage: (messageId: string) => void;
    handleStreamRequest: (messageId: string) => Response;
    emitEvent: (messageId: string, event: StreamEvent) => void;
};
```

### MCP Route (existing)
- `mcp/mcp-route.ts` — 30+ handlers including session start/end
- Auth via JWT + JWKS in `mcp/auth.ts`
- `createAgentSession()` and `endAgentSession()` functions in `mcp/mcp-queries.ts`
- `createAgentSession()` auto-promotes task status from "todo"/"ready" → "in_progress"

### PM Agent Pattern (reference)
- `agents/pm/agent.ts` — `runPmAgent()` using `ToolLoopAgent` from AI SDK
- Composes shared tools from `chat/tools/`
- Returns structured output + traced steps
- Chat agent invokes via `invoke_pm_agent` tool

### Existing Tool Composition
- `ChatToolExecutionContext` with actor types: `chat_agent | mcp | pm_agent | analytics_agent`
- `ChatToolDeps` provides surreal, embedding model, extraction model
- Tools are composable building blocks

### Project Conventions (from AGENTS.md)
- TypeScript, no `null`, use `undefined` via optional properties
- SurrealDB SCHEMAFULL, RecordId objects everywhere
- Fail fast, no fallback masking
- No backwards compatibility — breaking schema changes OK
- Versioned .surql migration scripts (zero-padded prefix)
- Tool descriptions concise, parameter guidance in Zod `.describe()`

## Requirements Summary

### Functional Requirements
- **FR-1 Task Assignment**: Assign ready/todo tasks to coding agent, validate context, create opencode session with MCP, transition status, create agent_session
- **FR-2 Agent Monitoring**: Subscribe to opencode events, forward to Brain SSE, live activity feed, stall/loop detection
- **FR-3 Review & Accept**: Show diff summary + session trace, accept (done) or reject with feedback

### Non-Functional Requirements
- Session creation < 5s
- SSE forwarding < 1s latency
- Agent session cleanup on abort/timeout
- One active agent per task
- Authority scoped to `code_agent`

### Walking Skeleton (Feature 0)
1. Backend route: takes task ID, creates opencode session, injects MCP config
2. MCP integration: agent calls existing Brain MCP tools
3. Status updates: agent updates task status via MCP
4. UI: "Assign to Agent" button, basic status indicator

